      "content": "The core principle of the First Amendment is that no person shall be compelled to hold a belief or act against their conscience, and this right is absolute. While the government has a compelling interest in public health and safety, it cannot use its power to force a specific religious belief onto an individual, as doing so would violate the very freedom the state is meant to protect. A double standard exists only if the government allows one group to act on their conscience while punishing another for the same action; the law must remain neutral and apply the same rules to everyone, regardless of their beliefs.",
