      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The First Amendment protects religious freedom, but it does not grant religious groups the power to override the rights of others. A secular state is not weakened by allowing exemptions; it is strengthened by ensuring that laws apply equally to all citizens, regardless of their beliefs. If a rule is designed to protect the community, it must be enforced uniformly to maintain the very equality the state claims to uphold.",
      "source": "target",
